BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the death of a
2 family member where the incident led to law enforcement
3 initiating an investigation may raise many questions for the
4 surviving family members even years slater. Law enforcement's
5 investigation and the ensuing report may provide some answers
6 and perhaps even closure for a family. The legislature further
7 finds that obtaining this information can be difficult. For one
8 Hawaii family whose son was murdered, it took seventeen years
9 and repeated assistance from a state legislator's office to
10 receive the closing report. For another family whose son was
11 killed during an incident involving law enforcement, the family
12 still has not received a copy of the report more than five years
13 after the incident despite state legislator involvement.
14 The purpose of this Act is to allow surviving immediate
15 family members of deceased persons for whom law enforcement
16 initiated an investigation to receive a copy of the closing
