3 SECTION 2. Chapter 52D, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
4 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
5 and to read as follows:
6 "§52D- Request for copy of police report by a surviving
7 immediate family member. (a) Each surviving immediate family
8 member of a deceased person for whom law enforcement initiated
9 an investigation shall, upon request, be provided a copy of the
10 closing report prepared by the investigating police department,
11 upon the conclusion of any criminal proceedings related to the
12 incident, the passage of five years after the report has been
13 completed, or the passage of seven years after the underlying
14 incident, whichever occurs first; provided that if the
15 investigation has been reopened in the six months before the
16 request, the investigating police department shall not be
17 required to provide a copy of the report to the family member
18 while the investigation is ongoing; provided further that upon
19 the conclusion of the reopened investigation there shall be no
20 further delay in providing a copy of the report to the
21 requesting family member.
